    "causal_summary": "Phase 009 implements pt-03 RQ-A3 + RQ-B3 + RQ-B4 as a single L3 packet. Sub-Phase 1 applies 3 P0 precondition fixes (causal-edges auto-provenance cap broadening, manual-edge overwrite guard, retention-sweep tier basement gap). Sub-Phase 2 ships shared feedback-aggregation reducer. Sub-Phases 3-5 ship three independent decision consumers: coco rerank weights (Python, ±0.10 clamped delta), session-trace causal-edge inference (TS, ENABLED edges at strength 0.3, deferred), learned retention/decay (TS, RetentionDecision = delete|extend|protect, tier-aware basement). Cross-language Python+TS. All consumers default-off; live mutation requires Phase-006 eval. Largest LOC budget of the 5 phases. P0 fixes mandatory before Sub-Phases 4 (Consumer B) and 5 (Consumer C); Sub-Phase 3 (Consumer A) independent of P0 fixes.",
